<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 4:13PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Cimarron County through 500 PM CDT...
At 413 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Black Mesa Park, or 22 miles northwest of Boise
City, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Black Mesa Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
